**Living Vedanta Library**

I especially appreciate Swami Ashokanand Ji's central point: **Bondage is not caused by movement, but by misidentification.** Nature never stops functioning, yet the Self never becomes a doer. When this is seen clearly, life continues outwardly as before, but inwardly there is freedom. That is the essence of the Gītā's teaching on **akartṛtva** (non-doership).
